headline: Legal threats are pushing Trump's tariff strategy in new directions. Don't expect more certainty.
summary: The Supreme Court won’t consider the fate of President Trump’s blanket tariffs until November, but the White House already appears to be making adjustments that could keep as many duties in place as possible if the administration loses.

headline: Tech stocks roll on and Pfizer soars after Trump deal
summary: In the deal, Pfizer got tariff relief by agreeing to align U.S. Medicaid drug prices with the lowest prices paid by other developed nations.

headline: Investing.com’s stocks of the week
summary: Investing.com -- Despite the U.S. government shutdown, U.S equities have performed positively in the last week, climbing to new highs, with the S&P 500, Nasdaq and Dow all on track for more than 1% gains.
